      "text": "Agree & Join LinkedIn\n\nBy clicking Continue to join or sign in, you agree to LinkedInâ€™s [User Agreement](https://www.linkedin.com/legal/user-agreement?trk=linkedin-tc_auth-button_user-agreement), [Privacy Policy](https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy?trk=linkedin-tc_auth-button_privacy-policy), and [Cookie Policy](https://www.linkedin.com/legal/cookie-policy?trk=linkedin-tc_auth-button_cookie-policy).\n\n [Skip to main content](https://www.linkedin.com/www.linkedin.com#main-content)\n\n# M. Ahmedâ€™s Post\n\n[M. Ahmed](https://in.linkedin.com/in/lsahmed?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n\nFull.Stack Developer â€¢ Student\n\n6mo\n\n- [Report this post](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Flsahmed_in-nextjs-15-params-must-be-awaited-activity-7305187607464878080-x-WL&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n\n\"In [Next.js](http://Next.js?trk=public_post-text) 15, 'params' Must Be Awaited Now\".\n[Next.js](http://Next.js?trk=public_post-text) 15 has moved towards asynchronous processing of route parameters (params). Now we are required to use the await keyword while accessing params. To make adjustments, make your component functions async and await the params before accessing their properties. For further information, please see the official [Next.js](http://Next.js?trk=public_post-text) documentation.\n\n[Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Flsahmed_in-nextjs-15-params-must-be-awaited-activity-7305187607464878080-x-WL&trk=public_post_like-cta) [Comment](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Flsahmed_in-nextjs-15-params-must-be-awaited-activity-7305187607464878080-x-WL&trk=public_post_comment-cta)\n\nShare\n\n- Copy\n- LinkedIn\n- Facebook\n- Twitter\n\nTo view or add a comment, [sign in